# 

<span key="1fec2a7222fb444a83a1b233c95db61f"><span offset-key="1fec2a7222fb444a83a1b233c95db61f:0">Family Promise Service Tracker</span></span>

<span key="9e6a3ff52f63406fbf9ad9e4214019ae"><span offset-key="9e6a3ff52f63406fbf9ad9e4214019ae:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span><a href="https://familypromise.org" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="e84db7e4185840feb339448b8452c4f9" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-52653_259-52654-237__"><span data-key="0f5df35fe6c04ba5842a5acc5a121716"><span data-offset-key="0f5df35fe6c04ba5842a5acc5a121716:0">Family Promise</span></span></span></a><span key="8d8701c03c2b4e67af78b04f72ddbcf8"><span offset-key="8d8701c03c2b4e67af78b04f72ddbcf8:0"> helps local communities coordinate their compassion to address the root causes of family homelessness. They tap existing local resources to empower families towards economic stability. Families come to them in crisis; they help them rebuild their lives with new skills and ongoing support. They address the issue holistically, providing prevention services before families reach crisis, shelter and case management when they become homeless, and stabilization programs once they have secured housing to ensure they remain independent.</span></span>

<span key="f63650419b8c47729de3a0b4f51ec3cf"><span offset-key="f63650419b8c47729de3a0b4f51ec3cf:0">Family Promise needs a way to track and visualize the services they provide external to the shelter to gain actionable insights.</span></span>

<span key="e9dcc2ec7e0d45ad8087cb30a7aeaf4b"><span offset-key="e9dcc2ec7e0d45ad8087cb30a7aeaf4b:0">Our goal is to build a generalizable monitoring and evaluation (M&E) platform that meets Family Promise's needs, with an eye toward additional potential use cases that would be useful for many other organizations.</span></span>

### 

<span key="069d1c06d5694225beac82bc97372525"><span offset-key="069d1c06d5694225beac82bc97372525:0">Setup postgres</span></span>

<span key="1b5207912a1b4fc9a16eb7a803055cfa"><span offset-key="1b5207912a1b4fc9a16eb7a803055cfa:0">There are 3 options to get postgresql installed locally \[Choose one\]:</span></span>

1.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">1.</span>
    <span key="a722cf4fa0de41d0b6310664019f55c6"><span offset-key="a722cf4fa0de41d0b6310664019f55c6:0">Use docker. </span></span><a href="https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="7a487be92fab4b5888bfd1fec19d6bd7" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-52653_259-52654-237__"><span data-key="12bf435d27f84888b92660f1ef68e481"><span data-offset-key="12bf435d27f84888b92660f1ef68e481:0">Install</span></span></span></a><span key="c0fc68873eb7443cb97c4aeca15dcceb"><span offset-key="c0fc68873eb7443cb97c4aeca15dcceb:0"> for your platform</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="f1f581b627a14abea245886f3df89a1c"><span offset-key="f1f581b627a14abea245886f3df89a1c:0">run: </span>`docker-compose up -d`<span offset-key="f1f581b627a14abea245886f3df89a1c:2"> to start up the postgresql database and pgadmin.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="24994af53aa84d1da6135547c19617e7"><span offset-key="24994af53aa84d1da6135547c19617e7:0">Open a browser to </span></span><a href="http://localhost:5050" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="02b3ae19a1504aa4a4d169a3cc643c46" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-52653_259-52654-237__"><span data-key="10492a56f64848dd84ac78f9dbb8db95"><span data-offset-key="10492a56f64848dd84ac78f9dbb8db95:0">pgadmin</span></span></span></a><span key="97cb7597c4014fcdaa8d54668792f2f1"><span offset-key="97cb7597c4014fcdaa8d54668792f2f1:0"> and you should see the Dev and Test server already defined.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="b5f3c087599a4279a5759f0ce5089316"><span offset-key="b5f3c087599a4279a5759f0ce5089316:0">If you need to start over you will need to delete the folder </span>`$ rm -rf ./data/pg`<span offset-key="b5f3c087599a4279a5759f0ce5089316:2"> as this is where all of the server data is stored (</span>*ONLY IF YOU NEED TO START OVER*<span offset-key="b5f3c087599a4279a5759f0ce5089316:4">)</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="b1dea1b1380a4d5a92573d2cf9292326"><span offset-key="b1dea1b1380a4d5a92573d2cf9292326:0">Upon logging into postgres admin on localhost (2nd dash above), you'll see the API-DEV server, but you will need to check if there is a "api-dev" database within that server, if not or if the databases </span>`api-dev`<span offset-key="b1dea1b1380a4d5a92573d2cf9292326:2"> and </span>`api-test`<span offset-key="b1dea1b1380a4d5a92573d2cf9292326:4"> were not created then you'll need to create them by right clicking databases, clicking create database, and adding a database for "api-dev" and then start over at step 1. You may need to grant system execution access to the .sh file in docker/pg/pg-init-scripts:</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="0493abc170ca4c52b12b00bc711fac2f"><span offset-key="0493abc170ca4c52b12b00bc711fac2f:0">Run following from within root: </span>`chmod +x ./docker/pg/pg-init-scripts/create-multiple-postgresql-databases.sh`</span>

2.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">2.</span>
    <span key="01a654042db1476dbfa7fe0d67f51483"><span offset-key="01a654042db1476dbfa7fe0d67f51483:0">Download and install postgresql directly from the </span></span><a href="https://www.postgresql.org/download/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="f8b17b3128224490a55f80cb6f52c960" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-52653_259-52654-237__"><span data-key="bfb72e4d3144469484506d2554707fa8"><span data-offset-key="bfb72e4d3144469484506d2554707fa8:0">main site</span></span></span></a><span key="278d77d8bf3046e7be96c2ad100cc753"><span offset-key="278d77d8bf3046e7be96c2ad100cc753:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="23ca55b7380047dd9216c774abe8d49f"><span offset-key="23ca55b7380047dd9216c774abe8d49f:0">make note of the port, username and password you use to setup the database.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="0af038417d8a4917929c04d48fa5630a"><span offset-key="0af038417d8a4917929c04d48fa5630a:0">Connect your client to the server manually using the values previously mentioned</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="dce0ef4b0208441d9cef98feb8c39b04"><span offset-key="dce0ef4b0208441d9cef98feb8c39b04:0">You will need to create a database manually using a client.</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="de2033662e8d4eb4a76445467d8171ea"><span offset-key="de2033662e8d4eb4a76445467d8171ea:0">Make sure to update the DATABASE\_URL connection string with the values for username/password, databasename and server port (if not 5432).</span></span>

3.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">3.</span>
    <span key="01eae50a5339496abb5018606dc5c9b3"><span offset-key="01eae50a5339496abb5018606dc5c9b3:0">Setup a free account at </span></span><a href="https://www.elephantsql.com/plans.html" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="eab65f6fd4c94485b2862f76fed49c2c" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-52653_259-52654-237__"><span data-key="88c9aff63c0a4441b2b1a3d59bd7fcad"><span data-offset-key="88c9aff63c0a4441b2b1a3d59bd7fcad:0">ElephantSQL</span></span></span></a><span key="99b0529d37dd453c95d289c04ae4c27b"><span offset-key="99b0529d37dd453c95d289c04ae4c27b:0"><span slate-zero-width="z">â€‹</span></span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="e0759f08b3ed42f29701c6d6679b4106">***Downside***<span offset-key="e0759f08b3ed42f29701c6d6679b4106:1">: JSONB column displays as </span>`[object Object]`<span offset-key="e0759f08b3ed42f29701c6d6679b4106:3">, so not good when testing/creating JSON queries</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="ad40c26f5b1d404298cf6ac8cdd91fdf"><span offset-key="ad40c26f5b1d404298cf6ac8cdd91fdf:0">Sign up for a free </span>`Tiney Turtle`<span offset-key="ad40c26f5b1d404298cf6ac8cdd91fdf:2"> plan</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="f59fc363953e4275abeebaa9c9336786"><span offset-key="f59fc363953e4275abeebaa9c9336786:0">copy the URL to the DATABASE\_URL .env variable</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="492f0125988c49598b0d303fc40928ee"><span offset-key="492f0125988c49598b0d303fc40928ee:0">make sure to add </span>`?ssl=true`<span offset-key="492f0125988c49598b0d303fc40928ee:2"> to the end of this url</span></span>

### 

<span key="b5d8741b618049289f5f8ee6c4acc22c"><span offset-key="b5d8741b618049289f5f8ee6c4acc22c:0">Setup the application</span></span>

    <span key="d9435051ecae49bb9c9666bc8c1b79c3"><span offset-key="d9435051ecae49bb9c9666bc8c1b79c3:0">create your project repo by forking or using this as a template.</span></span>

    <span key="7755f82d5e374e52ab0b378f0a1cb838"><span offset-key="7755f82d5e374e52ab0b378f0a1cb838:0">run: </span>`npm install`<span offset-key="7755f82d5e374e52ab0b378f0a1cb838:2"> to download all dependencies.</span></span>
